PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1780506355
OL,3,C'Death sentence': Woman whose dad died
OL,4,Cfrom pancreatic cancer calls for action
OL,6,FCarys' dad, Paul was diagnosed with
OL,7,Fcancer in the summer of 2022. Like
OL,8,Fmany patients he was not offered to
OL,9,Ftake part in any clinical trials which
OL,10,Fmight have slowed down his
OL,11,Fdeterioration.
OL,13,FCarys recalled when they were told he
OL,14,Fhad pancreatic cancer: "When we asked
OL,15,Fwhat was next. The answer was there
OL,16,Fisn't anything next."
OL,18,FPaul was offered chemotherapy but he
OL,19,Fbecame unwell quickly and died nine
OL,20,Fmonths after his diagnosis.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G3/7
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
