PN,46204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1780506355
OL,3,C'Death sentence': Woman whose dad died
OL,4,Cfrom pancreatic cancer calls for action
OL,6,FThe day her dad died Carys found out
OL,7,Fher uncle had also been diagnosed with
OL,8,Fpancreatic cancer. David was also not
OL,9,Foffered to be part of a clinical trial
OL,10,Fand died just four months after
OL,11,Fdiagnosis.
OL,13,F"It didn't feel real. That day didn't
OL,14,Ffeel real." Carys said.
OL,16,FShe described pancreatic cancer as a
OL,17,F"death sentence'". Less than 5% of
OL,18,Fpeople survive the disease for 10
OL,19,Fyears or more according to Cancer
OL,20,FResearch UK.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G4/7
OL,2,W+.-'*%/"-$+,(,'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
