PN,46206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F462A1780506355
OL,3,C'Death sentence': Woman whose dad died
OL,4,Cfrom pancreatic cancer calls for action
OL,6,FThey charity are calling for
OL,7,Fpersonalised treatments, a new system
OL,8,Fwhich fast-tracks patients onto
OL,9,Fclinical trials, and additional
OL,10,Ffunding to research new treatments for
OL,11,Fpancreatic cancer.
OL,13,FThe charity's CEO, Diana Jupp, said:
OL,14,F"Change is possible if this
OL,15,Fdevastating disease is prioritised,
OL,16,Fthe dramatic improvements in survival
OL,17,Ffor other cancers are proof of that.
OL,18,FPeople with pancreatic cancer deserve
OL,19,Fmore progress. More treatment
OL,20,Fbreakthroughs. They deserve a chance
OL,21,Fto survive."
OL,26,@vD@AOU}D@LO]
